[2026-04-18T16:40:01.386Z] [STDOUT] {"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/pulls/1643","id":3550055441,"node_id":"PR_kwDOPUU0qc7TmYwR","html_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/pull/1643","diff_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/pull/1643.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/pull/1643.patch","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/1643","number":1643,"state":"open","locked":false,"title":"Disable noisy Claude Code features in solve","user":{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"body":"## Summary\n\nFixes #1642.\n\nMakes Claude Code runs launched by `solve` quieter, deterministic, and fully auditable across hosts and Docker images.\n\n**Environment variables forced into the Claude subprocess and baked into both Dockerfiles:**\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_AUTO_MEMORY=1`\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_CRON=1`\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_TERMINAL_TITLE=1`\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_CLAUDE_MDS=1`\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_GIT_INSTRUCTIONS=1`\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_FAST_MODE=1`\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_FEEDBACK_SURVEY=1`\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_MOUSE=1`\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_ENABLE_AWAY_SUMMARY=0`\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_MAX_TOOL_USE_CONCURRENCY=4`\n- `DISABLE_FEEDBACK_COMMAND=1`\n\n**`~/.claude/settings.json` keys merged (preserving all unrelated user settings / env / attribution subkeys):**\n- `autoMemoryEnabled: false`\n- `spinnerTipsEnabled: false`\n- `awaySummaryEnabled: false`\n- `feedbackSurveyRate: 0`\n- `includeCoAuthoredBy: false`\n- `prefersReducedMotion: true`\n- `showThinkingSummaries: false`\n- `viewMode: \"verbose\"`\n- `attribution: { \"commit\": \"\", \"pr\": \"\" }`\n\n**How it's wired up:**\n- `src/claude-quiet-config.lib.mjs` holds the canonical required env/settings/attribution maps, the `buildClaudeQuietEnv` helper, and the idempotent `ensureClaudeQuietConfig` merge helper.\n- `getClaudeEnv()` in `src/config.lib.mjs` overlays the required env vars on top of `process.env` for every Claude subprocess.\n- `claude.lib.mjs#executeClaudeCommand()` calls `ensureClaudeQuietConfig({ log })` immediately before launching Claude — logs an auditable one-line summary at startup.\n- Both `Dockerfile` and `coolify/Dockerfile` set the env vars via `ENV` and seed a baseline `~/.claude/settings.json` with the same values plus attribution overrides, so the container is quiet even if `solve` is bypassed.\n- `docs/case-studies/issue-1642/` captures the issue/PR data snapshots and the upstream Claude Code documentation pages used to verify key names.\n\n## Reproduction\n\nBefore the fix, the focused regression failed because `getClaudeEnv()` did not force the quiet env vars:\n\n```text\nAssertionError [ERR_ASSERTION]: getClaudeEnv should force CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_AUTO_MEMORY=1\nundefined !== '1'\n```\n\nAfter the fix: `node tests/test-claude-quiet-config.mjs` passes and confirms:\n1. Every required env var is present on `getClaudeEnv()`.\n2. The merge helper adds every required settings/env/attribution key without clobbering unrelated user fields.\n3. A second merge on the already-correct file is a no-op (`changed: false`).\n4. Both Dockerfiles contain every required key.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node tests/test-claude-quiet-config.mjs` — passes\n- `node tests/useless-tools.test.mjs` — 22 passed, 0 failed\n- `npm test` — 41 passed, 0 failed\n- `npm run format:check` — clean\n- `npm run lint` — clean\n- `npm run check:duplication` — clean\n- `bash scripts/check-file-line-limits.sh` (with local `node_modules/` moved aside, matching CI job order) — clean\n- `node scripts/validate-changeset.mjs` — passes\n- `node tests/docs-validation.mjs` — passes\n- `node --check src/solve.mjs` / `src/hive.mjs` / `src/claude-quiet-config.lib.mjs` — all clean\n- `bash scripts/check-mjs-syntax.sh` — clean\n\n## Notes\n\n- No screenshots — runtime/Docker configuration work, no UI change.\n- A follow-up review comment lists additional env vars and settings from the official docs that **could** be set for our autonomous/Docker use case but were not applied in this PR, with the trade-offs, so the maintainer can pick which ones to enable next.\n","created_at":"2026-04-18T15:09:05Z","updated_at":"2026-04-18T16:39:59Z","closed_at":null,"merged_at":null,"merge_commit_sha":"528f1db6b4e889e4bf252b9fbf9e0759a17691af","assignees":[{"login":"konard","id":1431904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE0MzE5MDQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1431904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard","html_url":"https://github.com/konard","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/konard/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}],"requested_reviewers":[],"requested_teams":[],"labels":[],"milestone":null,"draft":true,"commits_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/pulls/1643/commits","review_comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/pulls/1643/comments","review_comment_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/pulls/comments{/number}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/issues/1643/comments","statuses_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/link-assistant/hive-mind/statuses/213e5bda7961ef0783ddbd024ff0512440082558","head":{"label":"link-assistant:issue-1642-51e94ad4ccf4","ref":"issue-1642-51e94ad4ccf4","sha":"213e5bda7961ef0783ddbd024ff0512440082558","user":{"login":"link-assistant","id":245352401,"node_id":"O_kgDODp_H0Q","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/245352401?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/link-assistant","html_url":"https://github.com/link-assistant","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/link-assistant/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/link-assistant/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/link-assistant/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/link-assistant/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/link-assistant/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/link-assistant/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/link-assistant/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/link-assistant/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/link-assistant/received_events","type":"Organization","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"repo":{"id":1027945641,"node_id":"R_kgDOPUU0qQ","name":"hive-mind","full_name":"link-assistant/hive-mind","private":false,"owner":