[2026-04-18T16:40:07.215Z] [INFO] Reproducible testing.
[2026-04-18T16:40:07.215Z] [INFO]    - When fixing a bug, create a test that reproduces the problem before implementing the fix. When you cannot reproduce the problem, you cannot verify the fix.
[2026-04-18T16:40:07.215Z] [INFO]    - When encountering logic bugs, write an automated test that fails due to the bug, then implement the fix to make it pass.
[2026-04-18T16:40:07.215Z] [INFO]    - When encountering UI bugs, capture a screenshot showing the problem state, then create a visual regression test or manual verification screenshot after the fix.
[2026-04-18T16:40:07.215Z] [INFO]    - When creating tests, prefer minimum reproducible examples, meaning the simplest test case that demonstrates the issue.
[2026-04-18T16:40:07.215Z] [INFO]    - When submitting a fix, include in the PR description: (1) how to reproduce the issue, (2) the automated test that verifies the fix, (3) before/after screenshots for UI issues.
