[2026-04-18T16:47:32.675Z] [INFO]           "command": "git add .changeset/quiet-claude-solve.md Dockerfile coolify/Dockerfile src/claude-quiet-config.lib.mjs tests/test-claude-quiet-config.mjs && git commit -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\nfeat(quiet-config): apply PR #1643 round-2 maintainer feedback\n\nAddress konard's review comment asking to:\n\n1. Re-enable Claude's built-in git/PR instructions — they are useful for\n   solve runs. Drop `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_GIT_INSTRUCTIONS=1` from both\n   `buildClaudeQuietEnv`, `getClaudeEnv` overlay, both Dockerfile `ENV`\n   blocks, and the baseline `~/.claude/settings.json env` seed. Mirror\n   the intent at the settings level with `includeGitInstructions: true`.\n\n2. Enable task tracking in non-interactive mode with\n   `CLAUDE_CODE_ENABLE_TASKS=1` so internal TODO items surface in logs.\n\n3. Enable turn resume with `CLAUDE_CODE_RESUME_INTERRUPTED_TURN=1` for\n   deterministic crash recovery.\n\n4. Make the bypass-permissions mode visible in `/status` and skip the\n   one-time prompt via `permissions.defaultMode: \"bypassPermissions\"`\n   and `skipDangerousModePermissionPrompt: true`. The existing\n   `--dangerously-skip-permissions` CLI flag is kept as belt-and-\n   suspenders.\n\n5. Preserve unrelated user-defined `permissions.*` subkeys (e.g.\n   `additionalDirectories`) by merging, same pattern as `attribution`\n   and `env`.\n\nRegression test updated to assert:\n- `CLAUDE_CODE_DISABLE_GIT_INSTRUCTIONS` is neither forced via env nor\n  written into the merged settings env block.\n- `claude.lib.mjs` still passes `--dangerously-skip-permissions`.\n- `permissions.additionalDirectories` is preserved across merges.\n- Every new key/value is baked into both Dockerfiles.\n\n`npm test` → 41 passed / 0 failed. `npm run lint`, `npm run format:check`,\n`npm run check:duplication`, `scripts/check-mjs-syntax.sh`,\n`scripts/validate-changeset.mjs`, `tests/docs-validation.mjs`, and\n`scripts/check-file-line-limits.sh` (with node_modules/ moved aside to\nmatch CI) all pass.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n)\"",
